              "quote": "The use of a foundational ontology mainly reduces semantic interoperability problems shown in open and dynamic scenarios, such as databases; allows integrating different ontological portions to compose an extensive domain and facilitates reuse since new ontologies can appropriate well-founded concepts defined in these ontologies.",
              "section": "2. Baseline"
            }
          ],
          "justification": "The paper describes the ontology as a means to reduce semantic interoperability issues across systems, implying its use in aligning different stakeholders or systems. While not explicitly mentioning meetings or real-time discussion, the context of interoperability suggests communication between systems or teams, satisfying the Communicating goal with moderate confidence."
